sequenceDiagram
    %% Greek-only execution sequence. This path computes Greeks without running
    %% splitter, metrics, or reporting stages.

    participant User
    participant Runner as Greek-only runner
    participant Loader as Input loader
    participant Normalizer as Column normalizer
    participant Resolver as IV/T/r resolver
    participant Engine as core.greeks.batch_greeks
    participant Writer as Output writer

    User->>Runner: Request Greek-only computation
    Runner->>Loader: Load prepared rows or raw chain + config
    Loader-->>Runner: Option rows
    Runner->>Normalizer: Normalize names and dtypes
    Normalizer-->>Runner: Canonical option rows
    Runner->>Resolver: Resolve model inputs
    Resolver->>Resolver: Compute T if expiry/as_of_date provided
    Resolver->>Resolver: Select IV source or existing iv
    Resolver->>Resolver: Select r, q, model, backend
    Resolver-->>Runner: Greek input contract + invalid-row reasons
    Runner->>Engine: batch_greeks(valid rows only)
    Engine-->>Runner: Computed Greeks for valid rows
    Runner->>Runner: Recombine with invalid-row NaNs
    Runner->>Writer: Write row-aligned Greek outputs and quality summary
    Writer-->>User: greeks.csv/parquet + summary
